'''Future Bank B.S.C.''' ({{Lang-ar|بنك المستقبل}}) is a [[commercial bank]] that was based in [[Manama]], [[Bahrain]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=61682426|title=Future Bank B.S.C.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-08-08}}</ref> It started as a [[joint venture]] by [[Ahli United Bank]] and two Iranian state-owned banks, [[Bank Melli Iran|Bank Melli]] and [[Bank Saderat Iran|Bank Saderat.]]<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/billion-dollar-sanctions-busting-scheme-aided-iran-documents-show/2018/04/03/37be988a-3356-11e8-94fa-32d48460b955_story.html|title=Billion-dollar sanctions-busting scheme aided Iran, documents show|last=Mekhennet|first=Souad|last2=Warrick|first2=Joby|date=2018-04-03|website=Washington Post|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-08}}</ref>

[[Central Bank of Bahrain]] closed down the bank in 2016 after Bahrain cut diplomatic ties with Iran.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/bahrain-iran-banks/bahrain-moves-to-close-irans-future-bank-idUSL8N15A29V|title=Bahrain moves to close Iran's Future Bank|last=Arnold|first=Tom|date=2016-01-26|work=Reuters|access-date=2018-08-08|editor-last=Smith|editor-first=Alexander|language=}}</ref> In 2017, [[Central Bank of the Islamic Republic of Iran]] licensed the bank to open a branch in [[Kish Island]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/economy-business-and-markets/65918/5-foreign-banks-licensed-by-iran|title=5 Foreign Banks Licensed by Iran|date=2017-06-06|work=Financial Tribune|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en-US}}</ref>
