{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = |name = Ibrahim Mohammed Awal|honorific-suffix = |image = Mohammed Awal.jpg |caption=Awal Mohammed visits Kenya for a business talks ahead of the Kenya Trade Expo Ghana 2017. |imagesize = |smallimage = <!--If this is specified, "image" should not be.--> |alt = |order = |office = [[Ministry of Business Development (Ghana)|Minister of Business Development]] |term_start = February 2017 |term_end = |president = [[Nana Akuffo-Addo]] |predecessor = |successor = ''Incumbent'' |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1962}} |birth_place = Ghana |death_date = |death_place = |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality = [[Ghanaian]] |party = [[New Patriotic Party]] |otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> |spouse = |relations = |children = 4 |residence = |alma_mater = Ghana Institute of Journalism, [[University of Wales]] |occupation = Minister of State |profession = Journalist, Marketer |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |religion = }}
'''Ibrahim Mohammed Awal''' (born 1962)<ref name="gog" /> is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] journalist, marketer, entrepreneur and politician. He also served as CEO of Graphic Communications Group and Chase Petroleum. He is a member of the [[New Patriotic Party]] and has served as [[Ministry of Business Development (Ghana)|Minister of Business Development of Ghana]] since 2017.
==Educational life== Ibrahim Awal attended [[Yendi Senior High School]] in the [[Northern Region (Ghana)|Northern Region]] of Ghana before proceeding to the [[Ghana Institute of Journalism]] in [[Accra]].<ref name="gra" /> He holds a Masters in Applied Business Research form the [[Swiss Business School]], Switzerland, and an Executive Masters in [[Business Administration]] from the [[University of Ghana Business School]], [[Legon]]. He obtained a Masters in International Journalism from the [[University of Wales]], United Kingdom. As of January 2017, he was pursuing a [[Doctor of Philosophy]] in Business Administration at the Swiss Business School.<ref name="gog">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/en/governance/ministers/3446-ibrahim-awal-mohammed-business-development | title=Governance Ibrahim Awal Mohammed –Business Development | publisher=Government of Ghana | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="gha" />
==Working life== After completing the school of journalism, Mohammed Awal joined the Graphic Communications Group Limited first as a reporter and later page editor.<ref name="sfa"/> He was promoted to the position of general manager for marketing after a brief stint as the advertising manager. He was appointed as [[Chief Executive Officer]] of the company in 2007.<ref name="sfa">{{cite web | url=https://www.primenewsghana.com/business/akufo-addo-appoints-former-graphic-md-ibrahim-awal-as-minister.html | title=Akufo-Addo nominates former Graphic MD Ibrahim Awal as minister | publisher=Prime News Ghana | date=12 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> He resigned in 2010 to take up the position of Managing Director of Chase Petroleum — a down stream oil marketing company.<ref name="gog" /> In 2009, he was awarded the Marketing Man of the year for his contribution towards marketing in Ghana by the Charted Institute of Marketing Ghana.<ref name="gra" /><ref name="gha">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Profile-of-Ibrahim-Mohammed-Awal-Business-Dev-t-Minister-Designate-500514 | title=Profile of Ibrahim Mohammed Awal – Business Dev’t Minister Designate | publisher=Ghana Web | date=12 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="peace">{{cite web | url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/politics/politics/201701/302951.php | title=Bio Of Ibrahim Mohammed Awal, Minister For Business Development | publisher=PeaceFM Online | date=13 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> At the time of his appointment, Mohammed Awal was the CEO of Marble Communication Group Limited, a private [[publishing house]] in Ghana.<ref name="gra" /><ref name="city3">{{cite web | url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/01/12/ceo-of-finder-to-head-newly-created-business-ministry/ | title=CEO of Finder to head newly created business ministry | publisher=Citifm Online | date=13 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref>
==Minister for Business Development== On 12 January 2017, Mohammed Awal was nominated by [[Nana Akuffo-Addo|President Akuffo-Addo]] for the position of Minister for Business Development.<ref name="gra">{{cite web | url=http://www.graphic.com.gh/news/politics/ibrahim-awal-nominated-by-akufo-addo-as-minister-designate-for-business-development.html | title=Ibrahim Awal nominated by Akufo-Addo as Minister-designate for Business Development | publisher=Graphic Communication Company | date=12 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="myjoyhu">{{cite web | url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/business/2017/january-13th/new-business-development-ministry-to-boost-private-sector.php | title=New Business Development Ministry to boost private sector | publisher=Myjoy Online | date=13 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> The ministry was a new ministry and is to formulate policies and facilitate the work of Ghana's private sector.<ref name="guta">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanatrade.gov.gh/Trade-News/businesses-welcome-new-ministry-of-business-development.html | title=Businesses welcome new Ministry of Business Development | publisher=Ghana Trade | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="puls">{{cite web | url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/business/new-ministry-businesses-laud-nana-addo-for-creating-business-development-ministry-id6046911.html | title=Businesses laud Nana Addo for creating Business Development Ministry | date=13 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> His appointment was hailed by the [[Ghana Union of Traders]], the [[Association of Ghana Industries]] and the general business community in the country with most wondering why it had not been established earlier under previous governments.<ref name="guta" /><ref name="puls" /> He was vetted by the appointments committee of the [[Parliament of Ghana]] on 7 February 2017.<ref name="citit">{{cite web | url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/02/08/well-help-more-women-to-own-businesses-mohammed-awal/ | title=We’ll help more women to own businesses – Mohammed Awal | publisher=Citi FM Online | date=8 February 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://quicknewsgh.com/2017/04/28/modernizing-ghanas-business-laws/minister-for-business-development-ibrahim-mohammed-awal/ | title=Minister for Business Development, Ibrahim Mohammed Awal | publisher=Quick News Ghana | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> During his vetting he made known to the committee that he would help set up 20 bid companies by 2020 to reduce unemployment.<ref name="citit2">{{cite web | url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/02/08/new-biz-devt-ministry-to-create-20-big-companies-in-4-years/ | title=New Biz Dev’t Ministry to create 20 big companies in 4 years | publisher=Citi FM Online | date=8 February 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref> Under this policy his ministry would help promote the interest of business by reducing interest rates, do away with nuisance taxes and speed up the rate for business registration while protecting locally manufactured goods from unfair competition from foreign imports.<ref name="citit2"/> Another policy he announced to the committee was to ensure that more women in Ghana could own their own business.<ref name="citit"/> He was approved by parliament and sworn in by President Akuffo-Addo on 10 February 2017.<ref name="sweqa">{{cite web | url=http://m.myjoyonline.com/marticles/opinion/akufoaddo-swears-in-final-batch-of-ministerial-nominees | title=Akufo-Addo swears in final batch of Ministerial nominees | publisher=My Joy Online | date=10 February 2017 | accessdate=29 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="gog2">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/en/media-center/news/3438-president-akufo-addo-swears-in-last-batch-of-ministers | title=President Akufo-Addo swears-in last batch of ministers | publisher=Government of Ghana | accessdate=29 July 2017}}</ref> In May 2017, he made it known that it was his ministry's plan encourage the private sector to grow the economy and triple annual [[gross domestic product]] to 200 billion [[cedi]]s by 2020.<ref name="gdp">{{cite web | url=http://managingghana.com/ibrahim-awal-eyes-gh%C2%A2200bn-gdp-2020/ | title=The Minister for Business Development, Mr Ibrahim Mohammed Awal eyes GH¢200bn GDP by 2020. | publisher=Managing Ghana | date=31 May 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref>
==Personal life== Mohammed Awal is Muslim and is married with four children.<ref name="gog" />
